.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:3:description: "Planned implementation sequence for adding the v4 compiled-routing directive, explicit legacy/ready onboarding, canonical manifest minting, and regression coverage to create-skill's parent-hub path."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:17:- Match phases to the stated scope; remove setup theater that does not change the outcome.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:19:- Over-planning, missing rollback, and treating assumptions as dependencies.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:31:| **Language/Stack** | Python 3 initializer, Markdown templates, pytest contract tests |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:34:| **Compiled dependency** | Canonical P3 minter, manifest store, freshness predicate, and data-driven runtime discovery |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:35:| **Compatibility posture** | Existing CLI calls default to legacy; agent workflow asks explicitly |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:39:The smallest viable change keeps the current generator structure and adds one parent-only state option. Both generated parent templates always receive the additive compiled-routing directive. The state option controls only the manifest lifecycle: `legacy` emits none, while `ready` calls and verifies the canonical P3 minter after router inputs are final.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:41:The implementation must not build a second compiler or freshness rule inside create-skill. It consumes the stable shared interfaces, updates the active and copy-from templates together, and expands the existing create-skill contract tests.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:46:<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:51:- [ ] P3 exposes a stable minter, manifest-location abstraction, freshness predicate, and new-hub runtime discovery.
