.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-227----
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-228-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-229-## 11. USER STORIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-230-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:231:- **US-001 (operator).** As the operator overseeing the cutover, I want the default-on question recorded with verifiable receipts and the settled ruling, so I can see how it was decided and override to flip-now if I choose, with full information rather than a narrative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-232-- **US-002 (skill author).** As someone creating a new hub via `create-skill`, I want compiled eligibility to follow from minting a manifest, so my skill onboards by a documented step and, until then, routes via legacy by construction instead of being silently half-wired.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-233-- **US-003 (maintainer).** As a maintainer editing a hub's routing inputs, I want CI to fail "re-mint required" when I forget to re-mint, so a silent revert to legacy becomes a loud, fixable signal instead of an invisible regression.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-234-- **US-004 (release owner).** As the owner of the eventual global flip, I want a per-hub serving-status readout and a documented `=0` kill-switch, so I can flip hub-by-hub, watch each land, and revert instantly if any hub misbehaves.
--
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-237-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-238-## 12. OPEN QUESTIONS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-239-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:240:- **Q1 (resolved).** The ruling is settled: adopt the phased path (default-on as a staged P4 outcome after P0–P3), decided on the analysis and reversible. An operator override to flip `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on now remains available but is not blocking; the steelman for flipping now is recorded in `decision-record.md` ("flip it when compiled does something legacy can't").
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:241:- **Q2.** For the P0 resolver-coupling remediation: promote `resolve.cjs` out of the spec tree into a stable runtime location, or keep it in place behind a path-integrity guard that fails loudly on a renumber? (Recommendation: promote; it removes the drift source rather than guarding it.)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:242:- **Q3.** Which single env profile hosts the P2 canary default-on (repo default staying off), and what parity + clean-fallback thresholds gate promotion from P2 to P3?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-243-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-244-<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->
