.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md-88-## How It Was Delivered
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md-89-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:90:Delivery follows the ordered gates in `plan.md`: an operator go-ahead to begin, P0 safety surface, P1 drift enforcement, P2 canary, P3 derived eligibility, and P4 staged cutover. Each stage records parity, status, rollback, and scorer-integrity evidence before the next stage can begin. The implementation stops at the first failed gate.
