.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md-155-
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md-156-1. **The ruling is reversible and overridable.** The settled phased path is a documentation decision; the operator may override to flip-now, and no runtime state depends on the ruling yet.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:157:2. **The flag is still undocumented in the environment reference.** That gap is P0 implementation work, not work performed by this authoring phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:158:3. **Drift and breakage are not yet distinguishable in the live verification surface.** The planned P0 harness change owns that distinction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:159:4. **Eligibility is still duplicated.** The P3 implementation has not replaced the current hand-maintained sets.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:160:5. **The resolver still depends on the current runtime path arrangement.** P0 must promote it or record and guard an approved exception.
