   153	## 5. TESTING STRATEGY
   154	
   155	| Test Type | Scope | Planned Tools |
   156	|-----------|-------|---------------|
   157	| Unit | Normalization and first-difference diagnostics | Vitest table tests |
   158	| Process | Child flag-on invocation and parent env isolation | `spawnSync` fixture wrapper |
   159	| Contract | Fresh eligible hub parity | Temp hub/manifest fixture plus same route gold |
   160	| Contract | Missing and stale manifest | Shared status adapter fixtures |
   161	| Negative | Fresh manifest with invalid JSON/sentinel, forced route divergence | Vitest failure fixtures |
   162	| Regression | Unchanged D1-D5 and existing verdicts when parity not applicable | Baseline report deep comparison |
   163	| Integrity | Frozen file hashes | SHA-256 before/after and test-time assertion |
   164	| End-to-end | JSON report, Markdown rendering, process exit | Programmatic `run()` in temp output directory |
   165	<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->
   166	
   167	---
   168	
   169	<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->
   170	## 6. DEPENDENCIES
   171	
   172	| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |
   173	|------------|------|--------|-------------------|
   174	| Default-on decision contracts | Internal | Available | Status ownership must stay single-sourced |
   175	| P0 stable front door and status cause | Internal | Planned | Compiled invocation or cause classification remains fragile |
   176	| P3 eligibility and manifest discovery | Internal | Planned | Harness would need a forbidden local hub list |
   177	| Current Lane C modules and tests | Internal | Available | Provide the immutable baseline and integration seam |
   178	| Seven hub registries | Internal | Available | Required for identifier normalization |
   179	<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->
   180	
   181	---
   182	
   183	<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->
   184	## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN
   185	
   186	- **Trigger**: D1-D5 baseline drift, false parity failures, environment leakage, live manifest mutation, incorrect drift classification, or frozen hash mismatch.
   187	- **Procedure**: Remove the orchestrator/report integration and new parity module from the active Lane C path; restore prior CLI/report behavior; retain diagnostic fixtures only if they remain inert; rerun existing Lane C suites and confirm baseline reports. The frozen files require no rollback because they are never edited.
   188	<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->
   189	
   190	---
   191	
   192	<!-- ANCHOR:phase-deps -->
   193	## L2: PHASE DEPENDENCIES
   194	
   195	```text
   196	P0 front door/status + P3 eligibility
   197	                 |
   198	                 v
   199	baseline -> parity module -> orchestrator/report -> fixtures/tests -> adoption
   200	```
   201	
   202	| Phase | Depends On | Blocks |
   203	|-------|------------|--------|
   204	| Setup | Stable P0/P3 interfaces | Core implementation |
   205	| Core implementation | Setup | Verification |
   206	| Verification | Core implementation | Lane C compiled-reality gate |
   207	<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-deps -->
   208	
