    10	# Implementation Summary: Lane C Compiled-Routing Benchmark Alignment
    11	
    12	<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->
    13	<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: impl-summary-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->
    14	
    15	---
    16	
    17	<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->
    18	## Metadata
    19	
    20	| Field | Value |
    21	|-------|-------|
    22	| **Status** | Planned |
    23	| **Date** | 2026-07-20 |
    24	| **Level** | 2 |
    25	| **Implementation** | Not started |
    26	| **Current Lane C path** | Legacy deterministic router replay only |
    27	| **Frozen scorer state** | Pinned and untouched by this documentation phase |
    28	| **Strict validation** | Planned after the full Markdown set is authored |
    29	<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->
    30	
    31	---
    32	
    33	<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->
    34	## What Was Built
    35	
    36	Lane C will gain a deterministic parity module around the existing scorer. For eligible route-gold scenarios it will preserve the legacy replay, invoke the real public compiled front door with a child-only flag-on environment, normalize both routing results, run the same gold evaluator twice, and require mutual routing equality.
    37	
    38	### Planned Implementation Surfaces
    39	
    40	| Area | Planned Files | Purpose |
    41	|------|---------------|---------|
    42	| Parity harness | `compiled-routing-parity.cjs` | Invocation, normalization, status, equality, and digest checks |
    43	| Orchestration | `run-skill-benchmark.cjs` | Eligible-row execution and distinct gate |
    44	| Reporting | `build-report.cjs`, report JSON schema | Render compiled reality without changing scores |
    45	| Verification | New Vitest suite and isolated fixtures | Prove fresh, divergent, drifted, missing, and broken states |
    46	| Documentation | Lane C README and CLI usage | Explain the new resolved mode and result block |
    47	
    48	No Lane C runtime file, fixture, report renderer, manifest, routing input, or frozen scorer file was modified by this planning phase.
    49	<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->
    50	
    51	---
    52	
    53	<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->
    54	## How It Was Delivered
    55	
    56	Implementation waits for the stable P0 front-door/status interface and P3 eligibility/discovery interface. After baseline reports and hashes are captured, the new module lands first, then orchestrator/report integration, then the isolated state matrix and non-regression suite. The frozen modules are imported and hashed only.
    57	<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->
    58	
    59	---
    60	
    61	<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->
    62	## Key Decisions
    63	
    64	| Decision | Rationale |
    65	|----------|-----------|
    66	| Keep compiled alignment outside the scorer | Preserves the pinned D1-D5 and route-gold baseline while adding a new observation path. |
    67	| Exercise the public front door in a child process | Tests the real flag and serving gates and prevents parent environment leakage. |
    68	| Evaluate both paths against gold before comparing them | Two equally wrong routes must not pass merely because they match each other. |
    69	| Compare routing fields, not hashes or generations | The requirement is decision parity; additive metadata is allowed to differ. |
    70	| Use shared status and eligibility interfaces | Prevents Lane C from inventing a local hub list or alternate drift meaning. |
    71	<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->
    72	
    73	---
    74	
    75	<!-- ANCHOR:verification -->
    76	## Verification
    77	
    78	| Check | Result |
    79	|-------|--------|
    80	| Current-state source inspection | Confirmed: Lane C does not invoke the compiled front door or set the flag |
    81	| Frozen file hashes | Planned baseline and after-change comparison |
    82	| Fresh legacy/compiled parity | Planned |
    83	| Divergence gate | Planned |
    84	| Drift/no-manifest/breakage matrix | Planned |
    85	| Environment and manifest isolation | Planned |
    86	| D1-D5 report non-regression | Planned |
    87	| Existing plus new Vitest suites | Planned |
    88	| Strict spec-folder validation | Planned |
    89	<!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->
    90	
    91	---
    92	
    93	<!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->
    94	## Known Limitations
    95	
    96	1. **Stable status and eligibility interfaces are pending.** Sentinel output alone cannot distinguish drift from breakage safely.
    97	2. **The current public front door still reaches a resolver beneath the spec tree.** The P0 remediation must land before this harness becomes a durable CI dependency.
    98	3. **The drift exit-policy boundary remains open.** Lane C must report drift distinctly; the operator must decide whether the benchmark or separate drift-CI job owns the non-zero process signal.
    99	4. **This phase covers deterministic Mode A only.** It does not add paid real-model verification or network activity.
   100	<!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->
   101	
   102	---
   103	
   104	<!-- ANCHOR:follow-up -->
   105	## Follow-ups
   106	
   107	- [ ] Finalize the P0 stable front-door and machine-readable status interface.
   108	- [ ] Finalize P3 eligibility and manifest discovery without a hardcoded hub map.
   109	- [ ] Decide whether Lane C or the separate drift-CI job owns the non-zero drift exit.
   110	- [ ] Implement the harness, orchestrator, report, fixture, test, and documentation changes listed in `spec.md`.
   111	- [ ] Capture and compare legacy D1-D5 baseline reports before enabling the new gate.
   112	- [ ] Re-hash and preserve the three frozen files throughout implementation.
   113	- [ ] Let the parent workflow generate `description.json` and `graph-metadata.json` for this spec folder; this leaf authoring pass does not create them.
   114	<!-- /ANCHOR:follow-up -->
