   117	
   118	---
   119	
   120	<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->
   121	## 4. REQUIREMENTS
   122	
   123	### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
   124	
   125	| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
   126	|----|-------------|---------------------|
   127	| REQ-001 | Consume the eligibility and fallback decision without redefining it. | create-skill calls the shared P3 minter/freshness interface and links to the decision packet; no local allowlist, freshness algorithm, or alternate fallback rule is introduced. |
   128	| REQ-002 | Render the compiled-routing directive on every newly generated parent hub. | The active scaffold and canonical parent template contain the exact block above; generated commands use the actual hub name; the existing prose router remains below as fallback. |
   129	| REQ-003 | Expose two deliberate generated states. | `--compiled-routing legacy|ready` is parent-only; existing CLI calls default to `legacy`; the higher-level workflow asks for a choice; output states either `legacy (no manifest)` or `compiled-ready (fresh manifest verified)`. |
   130	| REQ-004 | Mint real eligibility for compiled-ready hubs. | `ready` invokes the canonical minter after final router inputs exist, receives the canonical manifest location, and validates freshness through the shared predicate before success output. No synthetic digest or hand-authored manifest is accepted. |
   131	| REQ-005 | Fail closed without a half-wired success state. | Missing minter, mint error, malformed manifest, or stale digest produces a non-zero result and never prints compiled-ready. The output names the retained legacy fallback or diagnostic path explicitly. |
   132	| REQ-006 | Preserve legacy compatibility. | `legacy` emits no manifest, the generated directive falls through safely, existing `--kind parent` calls remain valid, and standalone scaffolding is byte-equivalent except for unrelated timestamp fields. |
   133	
   134	### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
   135	
   136	| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
   137	|----|-------------|---------------------|
   138	| REQ-007 | Add contract tests and package validation for both states. | Tests cover directive substitution, legacy no-manifest output, ready fresh-manifest output through a test minter, stale/malformed rejection, unknown option rejection, and unchanged standalone behavior. |
   139	| REQ-008 | Keep authoring documentation synchronized. | `SKILL.md`, README, parent reference, active scaffold, and canonical template describe the same option names, ordering, and status language. |
   140	<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->
   141	
   142	---
   143	
   144	<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->
   145	## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA
   146	
   147	- **SC-001**: A newly generated parent hub contains the same compiled-routing directive shape as the seven established hubs, with its own hub name rendered in the command and fallback sentence.
   148	- **SC-002**: `legacy` generation emits no manifest and is reported as legacy by construction.
   149	- **SC-003**: `ready` generation is reported as compiled-ready only after the canonical manifest exists and the shared predicate confirms freshness.
   150	- **SC-004**: A mint or freshness failure cannot be mistaken for compiled-ready output.
   151	- **SC-005**: Existing parent and standalone generation invocations retain backward-compatible behavior.
   152	- **SC-006**: The implementation adds no local eligibility list and edits no frozen scorer file.
   153	<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->
   154	
   155	---
   156	
   157	<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->
   158	## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
   159	
   160	| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |
   161	|------|------|--------|------------|
   162	| Dependency | P3 canonical minter, manifest store, and freshness predicate | `ready` cannot be truthful without them | Gate implementation on the stable P3 interface; never emulate it inside create-skill |
   163	| Dependency | Data-driven runtime hub discovery | A fresh manifest alone cannot route a hub if the runtime still uses a fixed hub map | Require P3 runtime discovery before advertising ready mode |
   164	| Risk | Active scaffold and copy-from template drift | CLI-generated and manually-authored hubs receive different directives | One contract test reads both templates and compares the normalized block |
   165	| Risk | Backward-compatible default hides an author choice | Existing scripts need a default, but agent workflows should not silently choose | CLI defaults to legacy; create-skill workflow asks explicitly and reports the selected state |
   166	| Risk | Partial scaffold remains after a mint failure | Files may exist although the command exits non-zero | Print a clear diagnostic and legacy state; do not write a success marker or synthetic manifest |
   167	| Risk | P4 later changes directive semantics | The generated block could become stale | Treat the active scaffold and seven hub directives as one lockstep surface in P4 |
   168	<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->
   169	
   170	---
   171	
   172	<!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->
   173	## L2: NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
   174	
   175	### Determinism
   176	
   177	- **NFR-D01**: Given the same hub inputs and P3 minter version, manifest minting and readiness classification are deterministic.
   178	- **NFR-D02**: The rendered directive differs across generated hubs only by the resolved hub name.
   118	| Existing contract test suite | Current path/naming regression coverage | Add two-state onboarding matrix | pytest result |
   119	
   120	Inventories before implementation:
   121	
   122	- Confirm every initializer call site and test that relies on the existing function signature.
   123	- Confirm both parent templates and every documentation pointer to them.
   124	- Confirm the P3 minter and predicate API, including error taxonomy and canonical returned path.
   125	<!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->
   126	
   127	---
   128	
   129	<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->
   130	## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES
   131	
   132	### Phase 1: Setup
   133	
   134	- [ ] Capture current generator output for standalone and parent fixtures.
   135	- [ ] Pin the approved directive text and the P3 minter/freshness API.
   136	- [ ] Define the state parser: parent-only `legacy|ready`, default `legacy` for existing CLI calls.
   137	
   138	### Phase 2: Core Implementation
   139	
   140	- [ ] Add the directive to the active parent scaffold and canonical parent template.
   141	- [ ] Update `init_skill.py` to render the hub name in both directive positions.
   142	- [ ] Add the ready-mode canonical mint and shared freshness verification after all router inputs are written.
   143	- [ ] Add explicit legacy and compiled-ready output; fail non-zero without a ready claim on mint/freshness errors.
   144	- [ ] Update create-skill workflow, README, parent reference, and package validation.
   145	
   146	### Phase 3: Verification
   147	
   148	- [ ] Extend create-skill contract tests for the full state matrix and template parity.
   149	- [ ] Run standalone and parent regression suites.
   150	- [ ] Run strict package validation on generated legacy and ready fixtures.
   151	- [ ] Run strict spec-folder validation and record any parent-owned metadata warnings separately.
   152	<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->
   153	
   154	---
   155	
   156	<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->
   157	## 5. TESTING STRATEGY
   158	
   159	| Test Type | Scope | Planned Tools |
   160	|-----------|-------|---------------|
   161	| Unit | Option parsing and parent-only guard | pytest |
   162	| Template | Exact directive block and hub-name substitution | Text extraction against both templates |
   163	| Generator | Legacy parent output | Temp dir; assert no manifest and explicit legacy result |
   164	| Generator | Compiled-ready parent output | Test minter; assert fresh canonical manifest and ready result |
   165	| Negative | Missing minter, stale digest, malformed manifest, unknown state | pytest parameter matrix |
   166	| Regression | Existing standalone and parent output | Existing `test_create_skill_contract.py` suite |
   167	| Package | Validator behavior for both states | `validate_skill_package.py --strict` on fixtures |
   168	<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->
   169	
   170	---
   171	
   172	<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->
   173	## 6. DEPENDENCIES
   174	
   175	| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |
   176	|------------|------|--------|-------------------|
   177	| Eligibility/fallback decision packet | Internal | Available | create-skill must not implement an alternate rule |
   178	| P3 canonical minter and predicate | Internal | Planned | Ready mode cannot be implemented truthfully |
   179	| P3 data-driven runtime discovery | Internal | Planned | Newly minted hubs would remain undiscoverable by the runtime |
   180	| Existing parent templates | Internal | Available | Both must move in lockstep |
   181	| Existing create-skill contract tests | Internal | Available | Provides the regression base |
   182	<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->
   183	
   184	---
   185	
   186	<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->
   187	## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN
   188	
   189	- **Trigger**: Generated directive mismatch, broken legacy invocation, stale manifest accepted as ready, standalone regression, or validator disagreement.
   190	- **Procedure**: Restore the prior initializer and parent templates; remove the ready-mode adapter from create-skill; keep generated hubs on the legacy path; do not delete or rewrite any existing hub manifest automatically. Re-run the pre-change generator fixtures before another attempt.
   191	<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->
   192	
   193	---
   194	
