.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:421:A `create-manual-testing-playbook` run is done when:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:423:- The package uses the canonical shape: root `manual-testing-playbook.md` plus kebab-case category folders of per-feature files, with no `snippets/` subtree and no separate `review_protocol.md` or `subagent_utilization_ledger.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:428:- The root playbook passes shared `validate_document.py`, per-feature files are manually spot-checked, and any remaining manual scope is documented honestly.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:434:The core executable workflow lives in this `SKILL.md`. Use these only for overflow detail, exhaustive examples, or template text:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:439:- `references/examples.md` - shipped reference playbooks and scaffold templates.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:440:- `assets/manual-testing-playbook-template.md` - root playbook scaffold.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:441:- `assets/manual-testing-playbook-snippet-template.md` - per-feature file scaffold.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:447:The source assets keep the filenames `manual-testing-playbook-template.md` and `manual-testing-playbook-snippet-template.md` until their separate source-file migration. Those filenames are authoring inputs, not emitted package names.
