.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:428:The template map, ordered authoring sequence, scenario-matrix rules, and naming
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:429:contract live in the [behavior-benchmark guide](references/behavior-benchmark/behavior-benchmark-guide.md).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:439:- **NEVER** give a shipped scenario file frontmatter or a `## OVERVIEW` heading; it opens at the `# <PREFIX>-NNN` H1 (the scenario template's own frontmatter, usage comment, and Overview are stripped on copy).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:444:- The owning mode-packet has a `behavior-benchmark/` package with an index, one scenario file per table row, and a baseline.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:454:A skill-benchmark measures whether a skill is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful; it is run by the deep-improvement Lane C harness (`/deep:skill-benchmark`), which emits a JSON+Markdown report pair per run. This packet owns exactly two things: the **storage convention** for a hub's `benchmark/` tree and the **template for its `benchmark/README.md` index**. It never authors the per-run report, the runner, or the scoring (see ALWAYS / NEVER). The full storage convention, run-label naming, and renderer boundary live in [`references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md`](references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md); the D1-D5 contract stays lane-local, cross-linked and never restated.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:458:A benchmarked skill or hub carries a `benchmark/` tree; every run writes its report pair into its own `<run-label>/` sibling folder:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:461:<skill-or-hub>/benchmark/
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:462:├── README.md              # optional hub index — templated here
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:466:├── <run-label>/           # one Lane C run; sibling to every other run
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:474:Every new `<run-label>` must match `^[a-z0-9]+(?:-[a-z0-9]+)*$`. Reject underscore-bearing or ambiguous labels instead of rewriting them after a run path has been selected. Existing legacy run folders remain historical references until their owning migration phase renames them.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:476:### Templates
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:478:| Output file | Template |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:480:| `<skill-or-hub>/benchmark/README.md` | [`assets/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-readme-template.md`](assets/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-readme-template.md) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:485:1. **Read the storage guide** — confirm the run-label naming convention and the frozen-baseline rule.
