.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:489:5. **Validate** the README with the shared sk-doc validator.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:493:- **ALWAYS** keep the README run-label index in exact sync with the folders on disk — one row per folder.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:494:- **ALWAYS** add a new run as a fresh sibling run-label folder and index row; keep `baseline/` frozen.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:497:- **NEVER** author a fill-in template for that report; templates here are for the `benchmark/README.md` index and INPUT fixtures/profiles only.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:502:- The skill or hub has a `benchmark/` tree following the convention, with a `baseline/` anchor and one sibling folder per run.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:503:- `benchmark/README.md` indexes every run-label folder, links the scoring contract and command, and carries no hand-authored report `.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:511:A model-benchmark run scores what a model or prompt framework produces against a fixed, held-out oracle; it is run by the deep-improvement Lane B harness (`/deep:model-benchmark`). This packet owns the **authored inputs** — the fixtures the model answers and the run profiles that drive a run. Both are data only. It never authors the evaluator, scorers, or reviewer-verdict contract (see ALWAYS / NEVER). The fixture-family taxonomy, profile shape, and lane boundary live in [`references/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-fixture-guide.md`](references/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-fixture-guide.md).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:518:system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:533:### Templates
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:535:| Output file | Template |
